1. Install Node.js and MySQL on your system.
2. Create a new directory for your project and navigate into it:
3. Write the following code in MySQL to create a database and a table:
        create database crud_app;
            use crud_app;
            CREATE TABLE users (
            Employee_ID INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
            Employee_Name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
            Employee_Age INT NOT NULL,
            Employee_Department VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
            Employee_Joining_Date DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
            );

            select * from users;



4. To run your Node.js application, execute:
            node index.js in order to execute the code